   - Summing over all zeros, we get an upper bound on the sum of `x^(ρ.re - 1) / ρ.im` by replacing `ρ.im` with `t_seq 0`.
   - Finally, we use the fact that `x^(ρ.re - 1) ≤ x^(σ₂ - 1)` (since `ρ.re ∈ (σ₂, 1]`) and the number of zeros is bounded by `N'(σ₂, T)`.

